<item>
            <title>[HBASE-940] Make the TableOutputFormat batching-aware</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-940</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-748&quot; title=&quot;Add an efficient way to batch update many rows&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-748&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-748&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we can batch updates but the auto-flushing is enabled by default. Make it that it is disabled for MR jobs outputting in a table and make sure that everything is sent in the end.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12406848">HBASE-940</key>
            <summary>Make the TableOutputFormat batching-aware</summary>
                <type id="4" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/issuetypes/improvement.png">Improvement</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.png">Major</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="1">Fixed</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="jdcryans">Jean-Daniel Cryans</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="jdcryans">Jean-Daniel Cryans</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Mon, 20 Oct 2008 17:50:20 +0000</created>
                <updated>Thu, 20 Sep 2012 22:10:38 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Fri, 24 Oct 2008 23:17:45 +0000</resolved>
                                                    <fixVersion>0.19.0</fixVersion>
                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12641420" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 21 Oct 2008 16:19:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch adds the improvement and cleans up some stuff. Also, I had some problems with the ITR because the BatchUpdate object seems to be reused, so the writeBuffer in HTable was filled 17 000 times with the same object when running TestTableMapReduce hence this code :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;while&lt;/span&gt;(values.hasNext()) {
-      output.collect(key, values.next());
+      BatchUpdate copy = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; BatchUpdate(key.get());
+      BatchUpdate old = values.next();
+      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt;(BatchOperation bo : old) {
+        copy.put(bo.getColumn(), bo.getValue());
+      }
+      output.collect(key, copy);

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12641433" author="dogacan" created="Tue, 21 Oct 2008 16:48:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Does this mean that after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-847&quot; title=&quot;new API: HTable.getRow with numVersion specified&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-847&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-847&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, if MapOutputValueClass is BatchUpdate, reduce will have to clone BatchUpdate objects before output.collect? Because if that is the case, I think a lot of MR jobs will break.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12641435" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 21 Oct 2008 16:54:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, well maybe the best solution would be to always do the copying in HTable.commit and we won&apos;t have any problem (here or elsewhere).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12641655" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 21 Oct 2008 22:55:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch puts a recopy constructor and does the copy in commit(). PE shows that it&apos;s not really slower.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12641797" author="dogacan" created="Wed, 22 Oct 2008 12:09:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 for latest patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12641804" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 22 Oct 2008 12:42:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately&#160;object&#160;creation&#160;may&#160;become&#160;a&#160;real&#160;problem&#160;in&#160;a&#160;big&#160;cluster&#160;with&#160;many&#160;writes&#160;if&#160;this&#160;patch&#160;is&#160;applied.&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
If&#160;TableReduce&#160;was&#160;not&#160;an&#160;interface,&#160;it&#160;would&#160;have&#160;been&#160;a&#160;good&#160;place&#160;to&#160;put&#160;this&#160;copy&#160;stuff&#160;since&#160;it&apos;s&#160;only&#160;useful&#160;for&#160;MR.&lt;br/&gt;
On&#160;the&#160;other&#160;hand,&#160;doing&#160;it&#160;in&#160;commit&#160;prevents&#160;weird&#160;situations&#160;where&#160;a&#160;user&#160;would&#160;have&#160;reused&#160;the&#160;same&#160;BatchUpdates&#160;over&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
and&#160;over&#160;and&#160;only&#160;the&#160;latest&#160;update&#160;would&#160;have&#160;been&#160;applied...&#160;many&#160;times.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12642566" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 24 Oct 2008 23:12:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Third option, put the recopy inside TOF. I think it makes a lot more sense.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12642567" author="stack" created="Fri, 24 Oct 2008 23:17:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Latest patch looks good to me.  Would just change the close on commit to just log an error and keep going rather than throw an exception (Whats the caller going to do if exception on close?)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12642570" author="stack" created="Fri, 24 Oct 2008 23:27:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;J-D calls out that the close that calls the RecordWriter call actually lets out Exceptions.  Makes my above criticism invalid.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
